  "text": "There is evidence of a higher use of somatic services [CITATION_1] and both a lower referral to a suitable specialty (i.e., psychiatry or geriatrics) [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] and an underutilization of mental services in the older individuals with depressive symptoms. These findings are similar to the data presented in this report (low use of mental health services and high use of benzodiazepines) [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Moreover, we found that depressed older individuals who were functionally impaired (who experienced difficulties in performing physical activity) were less likely to receive help.",
